{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% import 'macros/macros.html.twig' as macros %}
{% block title %}Home{% endblock %}
{% block body %}
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                Welcome to ESORaidplanner
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                ESO Raidplanner is a organizational tool for guilds in The Elder Scrolls Online. It is meant for
                planning guild events and integrates seamlessly with your guild's Discord server. You do not need any
                additional accounts to use this service, a Discord account is enough.<br><br>

                <div class="text-center">
                {{ macros.linkbutton(
                    path('auth_discord_login'),
                    'Login with Discord',
                    'primary discord-bg',
                    'discord',
                    true
                ) }}
                </div>

                <br>

                <h4>Information for Guild Masters</h4>
                In order to use ESO Raidplanner the owner of your Discord server must <a
                        href="{{ path('auth_discord_login') }}">log in</a> to this website once. Once
                logged in they will be able to activate the raidplanner on the Discord server. This process will also
                add the Raidplanner Bot to your server, so users can do all their event magic from within the Discord
                server!<br><br>

                <h4>Information for Guild Members</h4>
                If your guild is already using ESO Raidplanner, simply <a href="{{ path('auth_discord_login') }}">log
                    in</a> to our system once. We will automatically
                detect which guilds you are a part of. Once done you can use all the features of the website and the bot
                in the guilds you are a member of.<br><br>

                If you have any further questions you can always join our <a href="https://discord.gg/woeler" target="_blank">Discord server</a>.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
        <iframe src="https://discordapp.com/widget?id=342583943838826497&theme=light" width="100%" height="570" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0"></iframe>
    </div>
{% endblock %}